    dc:creator "Verrastro, Laura; Maneyro, Raúl; Da Silva, Caroline M.; Farias, Iraia" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "A new species of lizard of the L. wiegmannii group (Iguania: Liolaemidae) from the Uruguayan Savanna" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835711>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835713>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835715>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835697>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835717>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835705>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835707>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835709> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835711>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Head scales in dorsal, lateral, and ventral views. A: Liolaemus gardeli (ZVC-R 6823, male 6823 male, HL = 11.49 mm; HW = 9.76 mm); B: L. wiegmannii, population from Argentina (ZV-UNRC 3327 male, HL = 11.54 mm; HW = 9.8 mm); C: L. wiegmannii, population from Uruguay (UFRGS 3829 male, HL = 12.42 mm; HW = 9.69 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835711/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835713>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Holotype (ZVC-R – 6823) of Liolaemus gardeli." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835713/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835715>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Specimens paratypes of Liolaemus gardeli (ZVC-R 6823 (RML 2778), ZVC-R 6824 (RML 2779), ZVC-R 6825 (RML 2780), ZVC-R 6826 (RML 2781), ZVC-R 6827 (RML 2782), ZVC-R 6828 (RML 2783), ZVC-R 6829 (RML 2784), ZVC- R 6830 (RML 2785), and ZVC-R 6831 (RML 2786 – UFRGS 6630 – 6637)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835715/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835697>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. The geographic location of the Liolaemus sp. nov., Tacuarembó, Uruguay (31 ° 55 ' S, 51 ° 30 ' W), including the occurrence of other species of the group wiegmannii in Uruguay and surrounding areas. Administrative limits of the Uruguay departments are shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835697/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835717>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Aerial view of the dunes of the type-site for Liolaemus gardeli and a landscape zoom of the site highlighting bunches of herbaceous vegetation in the site. Manantiales Farm, Tacuarembó, Uruguay (31 ° 55 ' S, 51 ° 30 ' W)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835717/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835705>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Relationship of biometrical data between species of the genus Liolaemus, group wiegmannii living close to Liolaemus sp. nov. Snout-vent length (SVL); head width (HW); and, axilla-groin distance (AG). HW and AG were divided by SVL (the same letters mean significant differences between species)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835705/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835707>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Relation between the measurements of the parietal head scales (left and right) and the mental scale between species of the genus Liolaemus, group wiegmannii and Liolaemus sp. nov. living nearby. Right parietal scale (SPR); Left parietal scale (SPL) and length and width of the mental scale (PMS). All measurements were divided by head width (HW) (the same letters mean significant differences between species)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835707/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.835709>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Ventral color in life of the holotype (ZVC-R 6823) of Liolaemus sp. nov., A) (Photo: Dr. Márcio Borges Martins)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/835709/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

